'''Kayanarumi''' (賀夜奈流美, also written as 加夜奈留美 or 賀屋鳴比女) is a [[deity]] (kami) mentioned in the ancient text ''[[Engishiki]]''. The deity appears in the ''[[Izumo no Kuni no Miyatsuko no Kamuyogoto]]'' (Izumo Province 造神賀詞), a ritual prayer recorded in the text. ''Kayanarumi-no-Mikoto'' is primarily enshrined as a goddess at {{ill|Asuka-ni-Imasu Shrine|ja|飛鳥坐神社|12=draft|12=draft}} and {{ill|Kayanarumi-no-Mikoto Shrine|ja|加夜奈留美命神社|12=draft|12=draft}} in [[Nara Prefecture]].

== Overview ==
Kayanarumi does not appear in the ''[[Kojiki]]'' or ''[[Nihon Shoki]]'', and little is known about her origins, meaning, or legends.


=== Etymology ===
One theory suggests the name "Narumi" (鳴海) might symbolize "resonating sea," linking the deity to the concepts of sound and water. Scholars have speculated connections to male deities such as [[Torinarumi-no-Kami]] (鳥鳴海神) and [[Nunoshitomi Torinarumi]] (布忍富鳥鳴海神), both mentioned in the genealogy of [[Ōkuninushi]], though the exact relationship remains unclear.<ref>Shinchō Nihon Koten Shūsei, Kojiki: Kami Name Interpretations</ref> 


=== Appearance in Texts ===
In the ''Izumo no Kuni no Miyatsuko no Kamuyogoto,'' Kayanarumi-no-Mikoto is described as one of the guardian deities protecting the [[Imperial family]] alongside [[Ōmononushi|Ōmononushi-no-Kushimikatama-no-Mikoto]], [[Ajisukitakahikone|Ajisukitakahikone-no-Mikoto]], and [[Kotoshironushi|Kotoshironushi-no-Mikoto]]. The text states: 

* "賀夜奈流美命乃御魂乎飛鳥乃神奈備尓坐天皇孫命能近守神登貢置天"  
(*The soul of Kayanarumi-no-Mikoto resides in the sacred mountain of Asuka, protecting the Imperial descendants.*)

In ''[[Nihon Sandai Jitsuroku]]'' (January 27, 859 CE), Kayanarumi-no-Mikoto was elevated from Junior Fifth Rank, Lower Grade (従五位下) to Senior Fourth Rank, Lower Grade (正四位下).

== Shrines ==
Kayanarumi-no-Mikoto is enshrined in several locations in Nara Prefecture:

* '''{{ill|Asuka-ni-Imasu Shrine|ja|飛鳥坐神社|12=draft|12=draft}}''': Located in [[Asuka, Nara|Asuka Village]], Nara Prefecture. She is worshiped as the main deity.
* '''{{ill|Kayanarumi-no-Mikoto Shrine|ja|加夜奈留美命神社|12=draft|12=draft}}''': Situated in Kashiwano, Asuka Village.
* '''{{ill|Asuka Shrine (Nara)|ja|飛鳥神社|12=draft|12=draft}}''': Located in Nara City, enshrining Kayanarumi along with deities such as [[Kotoshironushi]], [[Ustukihime]], [[Fusokurihime]], and [[Sugawara no Michizane]].
* '''Daigyōji-sha (大行事社)''': A subsidiary shrine of [[Ōmiwa Shrine]] in [[Sakurai, Nara|Sakurai City]], where Kayanarumi is enshrined alongside [[Kotoshironushi]] and the eight-headed crocodile deity (八尋鰐).

